Ice Hockey VMI Hockey provides prospective students the opportunity to play competitive collegiate hockey at the nation s oldest state supported military college  The Institute holds the highest standards of integrity  leadership and camaraderie and that is no different for the Ice Hockey team  The program competes in the Blue Ridge Hockey Conference which is comprised of Appalachian State  Christopher Newport  East Carolina  George Mason  George Washington  Loyola  NC State III  Northern Virginia  Old Dominion  Radford  Richmond  Salisbury  The Citadel  UNC Charlotte  UNC Wilmington  and William   Mary  Since the club team s founding in 2004 it has produced four playoff appearances and an overall record of 48 42 4  VMI Ice Hockey draws players from all over the U S  from various house and travel league backgrounds  Players of all levels are encouraged to join the team  With its rigorous academics and physical fitness  VMI makes a Keydet hockey player well rounded on and off the ice  VMI is not only an institution of higher learning  but it prides itself in making every student an athlete  With a state of the art weight room which is over 7 000 square feet of space and has over 15 000 pounds of free weights and over 2 000 pounds dumbbell weights it provides the strength conditioning the Keydets need to perform well on the ice  Along with the weight room the Keydets are proud to play in one of the best home facilities in the American Collegiate Hockey Association  the LaHaye Ice Center in Lynchburg  VA      Ice Hockey VMI Hockey provides prospective students the opportunity to play competitive collegiate hockey at the nation s oldest state supported military college  The Institute holds the highest standards of integrity  leadership and camaraderie and that is no different for the Ice Hockey team  The program competes in the Blue Ridge Hockey Conference which is comprised of Appalachian State  Christopher Newport  East Carolina  George Mason  George Washington  Loyol